Defendant Rachel L Kopp in court, in custody by video with attorney Mackenzie Renner.  Andrew Herrmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 3:05 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for motion to modify bond on both files - 21CF487 & 22CF31. Court addresses  the potential co-signer who responds to Court's questions. Court informs co-signer as to risk of losing money and potential to be responsible for the $10,000.00 signature bond if defendant fails to comply with the bond. Based upon colloquy with the co-signer, Court grants the motion to modify bond to $10,000.00 ROR with $1,500.00 cash and co-signed by Carl Hicks. 
3:07 p.m. - Response by the State that based upon bond modification, State revokes bond and asks for trial dates. Response by the Court.
3:13 p.m. - Response by Atty. Renner that she is requesting speedy demand. 
Court sets both matters for speedy trial. Court in recess.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 20, 2022 at 03:00 pm.  Jury trial - 12 person scheduled for April 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
